### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

### Get all Software Engineering records
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/software-engineering
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Get Software Engineering by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/software-engineering/1
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Create a new Software Engineering record
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/software-engineering
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Java Development",
  "techstack": "Spring Boot, Hibernate, MySQL"
}

### Create another Software Engineering record
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/software-engineering
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Full Stack Web Development",
  "techstack": "React, Node.js, PostgreSQL"
}

### Create a third Software Engineering record
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/software-engineering
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "DevOps Engineering",
  "techstack": "Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD, AWS",
  "learningPath": "Linux -> Containerization -> Orchestration -> Cloud"
}

### Update Software Engineering record (ID: 1)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/software-engineering/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Advanced Java Development",
  "techstack": "Spring Boot 3, Spring AI, Hibernate, MySQL 8",
  "learningPath": "Beginner -> Intermediate -> Advanced -> Expert"
}

### Update Software Engineering record (ID: 2)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/software-engineering/2
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Modern Full Stack Web Development",
  "techstack": "React 18, Next.js, Node.js, TypeScript, PostgreSQL",
  "learningPath": "HTML/CSS -> JavaScript -> React -> Full Stack"
}

### Delete Software Engineering record (ID: 3)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/software-engineering/4
